  <discussion>Shoots of Campylium stellatum often look like small stars when seen from above in the field. The species is closely related to C. protensum, from which it differs in having a more erect growth, slightly larger size, and relatively shorter leaf acumen. Paraphyllia have never been seen in C. stellatum, whereas scattered plants of C. protensum have a few paraphyllia.</discussion>
